<div id="review_1581763897" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1581763897" />
    <a title="Carol" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23315273-carol"><img alt="Carol" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1546293743p2/23315273.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1581763897?book_show_action=true">Oct 15, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carol" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carol" href="/user/show/23315273-carol">Carol</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23315273-carol?shelf=translated">translated</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23315273-carol?shelf=books-i-own">books-i-own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23315273-carol?shelf=not-united-states">not-united-states</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23315273-carol?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23315273-carol?shelf=eastern-europe">eastern-europe</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1581763897" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18407898508734264860">Embers presents some of the loveliest, most elegant writing I have encountered this year. At its core, however, it is an overlong ramble of a soliloquy that should have been reduced to a stunning short story. It&apos;s an easy enough read, full of the philosophical queries and conclusions of its aged General about the meaning of life, love, honor, killing, obligation, M-M friendship. But the guest is permitted only 5-8 lines. He can&apos;t get a word in edgewise. And Krisztina? She has no voice. <br/><br/>I would l</span>
  <span id="freeText18407898508734264860" style="display:none">Embers presents some of the loveliest, most elegant writing I have encountered this year. At its core, however, it is an overlong ramble of a soliloquy that should have been reduced to a stunning short story. It's an easy enough read, full of the philosophical queries and conclusions of its aged General about the meaning of life, love, honor, killing, obligation, M-M friendship. But the guest is permitted only 5-8 lines. He can't get a word in edgewise. And Krisztina? She has no voice. <br /><br />I would like to read the novel Marai might have written about the ninety-one year old Nini. She captured my interest as none of the other characters did. Early on, it seemed as if Marai intended to make her more central to the plot, but alas, he chose otherwise.<br /><br />I am glad I read Embers and will look for others of Marai's novels as they become available in English translations; however, I will not press this one into friends' hands and insist that they do so. </span>
  <a data-text-id="18407898508734264860" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


