<div id="review_1931035081" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1931035081" />
    <a title="Josh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6041973-josh"><img alt="Josh" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1616360569p2/6041973.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1931035081?book_show_action=true">Mar 04, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Josh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Josh" href="/user/show/6041973-josh">Josh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780375407567" href="/book/show/922091.Embers">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6041973-josh?shelf=2017">2017</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1931035081" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6469150822052457169"><b>(4.5)</b> This is quite the case study into how the questioning of reason can keep a person alive until that question is answered: forty-one years, memories as if they were from yesterday, holding on, never leaving, keeping that thought, those questions betwixt a myriad of synapses firing endlessly until the time comes to explode forth with this torrent of misery, of elation, flooding; at last, he can finally die.<br/><br/>Many have given this a &apos;one&apos; star based on the fact that Henrik, the main character, ru</span>
  <span id="freeText6469150822052457169" style="display:none"><b>(4.5)</b> This is quite the case study into how the questioning of reason can keep a person alive until that question is answered: forty-one years, memories as if they were from yesterday, holding on, never leaving, keeping that thought, those questions betwixt a myriad of synapses firing endlessly until the time comes to explode forth with this torrent of misery, of elation, flooding; at last, he can finally die.<br /><br />Many have given this a 'one' star based on the fact that Henrik, the main character, ruminates and speculates throughout the whole book and then decides not to hear <b>the answers</b>. We do not always need an auditory answer to <i>know</i>.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6469150822052457169" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


